  "prompt": "What are the functions of knee pads?",
  "response": "Knee pads serve several important functions, including:\n\n1. **Protection**: They shield the knees from impacts, abrasions, and injuries that can occur during activities like sports, construction work, gardening, and other physical tasks. The padding helps absorb shock and reduces the risk of damage to the knee joint and surrounding tissues.\n\n2. **Comfort**: Knee pads provide cushioning that enhances comfort when spending a lot of time on your knees, such as when installing flooring, gardening, or engaging in certain exercises. This cushioning can help prevent pain and discomfort.\n\n3. **Support**: Knee pads can offer additional support to the knee joint, helping to stabilize it. This support is particularly beneficial to individuals with existing knee issues or those recovering from knee injuries, as it can help prevent further damage.\n\n4. **Injury Prevention**: By providing both impact protection and joint stability, knee pads can help prevent common knee injuries, such as bruises, cuts, sprains, and strains. This preventive measure is crucial for athletes and workers in high-risk environments.\n\n5. **Enhanced Performance**: In sports, knee pads can help athletes perform better by reducing the fear of injury and allowing them to focus on their movements and game strategy. This psychological benefit can contribute to improved performance.\n\n6. **Versatility**: Knee pads are designed for various purposes and can be customized to fit different activities. There are knee pads specifically made for sports like volleyball, basketball, and skateboarding, as well as those designed for professional use in construction or military applications.\n\nOverall, knee pads are a valuable accessory for anyone looking to protect and support their knees during physical activities.",
